	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64641416"><p>I did laugh a bit when I read that some people couldn't get free drinks at work because the machine refused to operate.  On the other hand, if someone needed cash, and many of the ATMs weren't working...  There are bigger problems here than just cash or not.  We've got too many single points of failure proping up civilizatgion.  Redundancy is too expensive, so it gets discarded.  The route-around-errors Arpanet is now Internet with critical hubs and services.</p></div>
