	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64642752"><p>Redundancy and heterogeneity are important in critical systems. I'm not opposed to cashless systems, I posit that removing alternatives reduces redundancy and heterogeneity of a critical system. Additionally, having two competing systems can optimize both, as I noted in my original post.</p><p><span class="substr"> </span> <b>From an operational standpoint, the importance of redundancy and heterogeneity are demonstrated repeatedly:</b> <br>With the Crowdstrike incident, only Windows PCs were affected. Linux and Mac PCs not affected.<br>I've seen ransomware in</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64642752">

