	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64641566">This is a (granted, pretty egregious) one-off.  Microsoft will certainly look for a way to mitigate the risk of this happening again (because they ended up with a share of the blame despite no agency in the actual failure).  Crowdstrike will certainly get a few new empty desks all the way up to at least one in the middle-office level of the organization and all of their front-line grunts will learn a valuable lesson as some number of devs, admins and maybe even engineers will be tossed under the bus - a truly horrific and sensational show, BTW.</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64641566">
